commit.message: RELEASE: 0.8.6
Keep the initial header name after the bearer token log formatting
DMC-1376: Also account for the "TransferHeaderAuthorization" header in the bearer token processing
Update release notes in preparation for v0.8.6 release

DMC-1376: Configurable behavior between masking the "Authorization" header with Xs or printing the 7 leading and trailing characters of the bearer token.

The behavior switch is done via the "DAVIX_FORMAT_BEARER_TOKEN" environment variable.
By default, Davix will mask the "Authorization" header with Xs.

If the header must be formatted but the "Bearer ..." part is not long enough, then Davix will fallback to the masking solution.
Rename header helper function from "_tolower(..)" to "transform_to_lower(..)" to avoid build conflicts on MacOS (fixes #115)
Use sed in a more POSIX compliant way

DMC-1401: Handle subtle length/size differences when calling the XML parser

By using the "std::vector::size()" call, the null terminator character also
became part of the parsable content. To avoid subtle length/size differences,
the content is transformed into a string first, which is then passed
to the XMl parser function

Do not hardcode error numbers

Test fails when EBADF != 9:

[----------] 7 tests from ContentProvider
[ RUN      ] ContentProvider.Fd
./test/unit/content-provider.cpp:93: Failure
Expected equality of these values:
  provider.pullBytes(buffer, 3)
    Which is: -1073741833
  -9
[  FAILED  ] ContentProvider.Fd (0 ms)

From /usr/include/i386-gnu/bits/errno.h:
  EBADF                          = 0x40000009,  /* Bad file descriptor */
DMC-1407: Initialize the Davix HTTP-TPC "ipflag" field to the default "IPtype::undefined" value
CI: Use a fixed number of characters in the commit reference name when building testing RPMs. This will ensure consistent RPM release git hash between different platforms

Support the NVHPC compiler

This compiler does not support the -fstack-protector-all flag, which is therefore removed from ReleaseDebugAutoFlags.cmake.
CI: Enable verbose mode for "ci/replace-directory.sh" script
DMC-1394: Header comparison should be case-insensitive for the libcurl backend as well
RELEASE: 0.8.5

Address "CVE-2023-38545" in bundled curl library (v7.69).

The patch is applied during the CMake preparation step, before compiling the bundled  curl source code.
Closes davix#107
CI: Update the EOS destination repository location according to the new naming convention
CI: Update the publisher script to Python3 syntax

CI: Update the publish jobs to use the "gitlab-eos/alma9" image. Also, as the gitlab-CI runner infrastructure has changed, the "docker-privileged-xl" tag must be used

https://cern.service-now.com/service-portal?id=outage&n=OTG0078219

Add git mailmap file

This file is used to map author and committer names and email addresses
to canonical real names and email addresses. This is useful when using
git blame, git shortlog, etc. For more information, see gitmailmap(5).
DMC-1388: Debian Buster build
DMC-1387: Fedora38 build
DMC-1379: Alma8 and Alma9 builds
Update release notes for release 0.8.4
RELEASE: 0.8.4

Don't downgrade the C++ version

The cmake configuration adds a compiler flag to set the C++ version to
C++11. This happens even if the default C++ version for the GCC
compiler version used is higer than C++11. In this case the flag
downgrades the version.

Since system libraries and headers can use features compatible with
the default C++ version of the default compiler, downgrading the C++
version might make some system libraries incompatible with this
setting.

The recent update of googletest in Fedora requires C++ 14.
The gcc version in Fedora Rawhide is currently 13.

C++ 17 is the default since GCC 11.
C++ 14 is the default since GCC 6.1.

This PR drops the addition of the -std=c++11 flag if the GCC version
is 6.1 or greater. With this change the code can be compiled on Fedora
Rawhide without triggering errors:

/usr/include/gtest/internal/gtest-port.h:270:2: error: #error C++
versions less than C++14 are not supported.
DMC-1361: Modify the "ne_davix_logger" function to recognize header messages and propagate them with a higher log verbosity
Improve the condition which detects whether the bundled curl is a git repository or not

Do not stop the build if the "git checkout" step fails during the curl patch step.

The "git checkout" is there to allow running cmake/make multiple times in a development environment. For the RPM build environment, there is no ".git" repository as the build happens directly from the extracted sources

Address "CVE-2022-32221" in the bundled curl library (v7.69).

The patch is applied during the CMake preparation step, before compiling the bundled curl source code.
Closes davix #102
